cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.solver
Interface Solver

All Known Implementing Classes:
AlgorithmCompareSolver, BaseSolver, MedianSolver, MultiSolver, ProblemCompareSolver, SimpleSolver
public interface Solver

Base of all solvers, defines methods required for solver to be used in JCOP.

addStopCondition

void addStopCondition(StopCondition stopCondition)
Adds new stop condition to list. All stop conditions are in OR relation, eg. al least one must be met to end run cycle.

Note that stop condition is automatically registered as listener, so do NOT add it again using addListener(cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.solver.message.MessageListener)!

Parameters:
stopCondition - new stop condition

isConditionMet

boolean isConditionMet()
Checks if at least one condition is met. If yes, returns true, otherwise returns false.

Returns:
true if at least one condition is met

addListener

void addListener(MessageListener messageListener)
Adds new listener to solver.

Note that all stopConditions added via addStopCondition(cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.solver.condition.StopCondition) are automatically registered as listeners so do NOT add them again.

Parameters:
messageListener - new message listener to be registered
